				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Wizardry Online - An MMO with permadeath
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1760835">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Wow, I never even knew EQ had a permadeath server.  I have tried playing a &quot;permadeath-like&quot; character in a couple of games (EQ, EQ2).  I allowed myself to continue playing if I died to a server drop or severe lag, but other than that I allowed myself one death.  I think the best I made was level 21 in EQ2 before dying.  It really adds a dimension to the game.  I'm considering trying it out in GW2, but there are so many events where death is nearly instant if you happen to have it spawn on you... not sure how that will work out. Wonder if there's an achievement for reaching level 80 without dying?
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
